data.title: National Benzole petrol advert - 1956
data.meta_description: National Benzole was a big petrol brand in the UK - Benzole being the additive manufactured by British Benzole, a company that produced the additive as a coal tar/gas by-product. The Mercury, with winged helmet, was the company's trademark.
